A RESOLUTION
1 Congratulating the Georgia Electric Membership Corporation on 85 years of service and
2 recognizing February 10, 2025, as Georgia EMC Day at the state capitol; and for other
3 purposes.
4 WHEREAS, in 1940, the Superior Court of the State of Georgia approved the charter of the
5 Georgia Rural Power Reserve EMC (now Georgia EMC), and its seven founders held a
6 special meeting at the Lanier Hotel in Macon wherein officers were elected and bylaws
7 approved; and
8 WHEREAS, EMCs are member-owned not-for-profit utilities that collectively serve
9 approximately 4.4 million people, nearly half of Georgia's population, across 73 percent of
10 the state's land area; and
11 WHEREAS, Georgia EMC is the statewide trade association representing the state's 41
12 EMCs, Oglethorpe Power Corp., Georgia Transmission Corp., and Georgia System
13 Operations Corp.; and
