14 WHEREAS, for the past 85 years, Georgia EMC has represented this network of member
15 cooperatives, who are committed to providing safe, reliable, and affordable electricity to
16 communities across the state, along with other essential services such as broadband; and
17 WHEREAS, as a result of more than eight decades of dedicated effort to improve the quality
18 of life in rural Georgia, many electric cooperatives enjoy a value to their communities that
19 goes beyond their ability to simply provide reliable light, heat, and broadband services, with
20 communities depending on them for economic development initiatives, civic leadership,
21 commitment to local job creation, consumer advocacy, support for youth and education
22 programs, charitable giving, and volunteerism efforts; and
23 WHEREAS, Georgia's electric cooperatives are proud to be considered essential corporate
24 participants in the state's responsible growth and development, and Georgia EMC looks
25 forward to many more years of service to its member cooperatives as they continue providing
26 essential electric and related services for Georgians.
27 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
28 the members of this body congratulate the Georgia Electric Membership Corporation for 85
29 years of service and recognize February 10, 2025, as Georgia EMC Day at the state capitol.
30 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
31 and directed to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to the
32 public and the press.
